12:14.078 --> 12:17.184
Did you ever pause
to think about that?

12:21.050 --> 12:22.672
I'm sorry.

12:22.672 --> 12:25.365
I'm sorry, too, for having to
put my hands on you.

12:25.365 --> 12:27.712
But it's my job
to protect my child.

12:28.748 --> 12:30.819
[ Clears throat ]

12:30.819 --> 12:33.097
I've had a hard time
going back to Queens

12:33.097 --> 12:34.615
since Mom's funeral.

12:35.582 --> 12:37.860
How are you holding up?

12:37.860 --> 12:41.346
All is fine when
you walk in the path of Jesus.

12:41.346 --> 12:43.935
[ Scoffs ]

12:43.935 --> 12:46.006
Amen.

12:46.006 --> 12:48.629
Frank Black: Oh, man, I'll
tell you, the coldest MCs
are always the women.

12:48.629 --> 12:50.908
That's why I always work
with the ladies, you know?

12:50.908 --> 12:53.013
I create a space
and I let their voices shine.

12:53.013 --> 12:54.946
Now, this right here,
this is Hood Honey.

12:54.946 --> 12:58.156
She spits fire,
she looks like fire.

12:58.156 --> 13:00.020
[ Keyboard clacking ]

13:00.020 --> 13:03.679
♪♪

13:03.679 --> 13:05.577
I discovered her
in a show in Compton.

13:05.577 --> 13:07.165
She about to be
a superstar.

13:07.165 --> 13:09.581
Yeah, I'm about to go
from Hood Honey to hood rich

13:09.581 --> 13:11.066
thanks to
my mentor Frank.

13:11.066 --> 13:12.412
Eric:
Jojo has class tonight?

13:12.412 --> 13:14.138
She said
she wanted to go to the movies.

13:14.138 --> 13:15.484
Yo,
you heard me?

13:15.484 --> 13:18.590
You think you can get me
a contact on Hood Honey?

13:25.563 --> 13:27.185
[ Chuckles ]

13:34.468 --> 13:35.884
Flan de queso.

13:35.884 --> 13:37.713
Oh.

13:37.713 --> 13:39.370
I thought the Louis bag
was a funny twist.

13:39.370 --> 13:40.612
Oh.

13:40.612 --> 13:43.029
You know, flan de queso
isn't easy to find.

13:43.029 --> 13:45.238
Then Eric told me about a place
the two of you went to.

13:45.238 --> 13:46.756
You know
I'm on a pre-show diet.

13:46.756 --> 13:48.034
Promise I won't tell
your trainer.

13:48.034 --> 13:50.070
You had to go to Eric to find
something special for me?

13:50.070 --> 13:51.658
The name
of a restaurant.
Whatever.

13:51.658 --> 13:52.935
You're serious?

13:52.935 --> 13:54.281
You're seriously mad?

13:54.281 --> 13:55.455
[ Sighs ]

13:55.455 --> 13:57.837
Would you be mad
if it were actually a purse?

13:57.837 --> 13:58.838
Don't insult me.

13:58.838 --> 14:01.150
That seems impossible
at the moment.

14:02.220 --> 14:04.050
Look, look,
I'm sorry.

14:04.050 --> 14:06.017
I tried
to do something nice.

14:06.017 --> 14:07.950
Clearly,
I missed the mark.
I'm not hungry.

14:07.950 --> 14:10.470
I'm tired, I'm stressed about
the performance.

14:10.470 --> 14:12.023
Let's chill then.
Reset.

14:12.023 --> 14:13.749
Let's not
talk about work

14:13.749 --> 14:17.270
or flan or any food of any kind
and just chill.

14:17.270 --> 14:18.305
I appreciate it,

14:18.305 --> 14:20.204
but I'm gonna need
a little time.

14:20.204 --> 14:21.861
I love you.

14:21.861 --> 14:24.242
Thanks.

14:25.554 --> 14:27.211
[ Door closes ]

14:28.281 --> 14:30.007
[ Knock on door ]

14:32.354 --> 14:33.803
Hey.

14:33.803 --> 14:35.426
Leah.

14:35.426 --> 14:37.290
Naomi.
Thank you for coming.

14:37.290 --> 14:39.395
I always wondered
when someone would call

14:39.395 --> 14:40.880
to ask about Frank.

14:40.880 --> 14:43.192
I didn't expect it
to be you.

14:43.192 --> 14:45.022
Come in.

14:47.576 --> 14:49.612
One second.

14:49.612 --> 14:53.478
♪♪

14:53.478 --> 14:54.479
[ Door closes ]

14:54.479 --> 14:57.206
Let's talk.

14:59.726 --> 15:04.282
I was 16
doing a talent show in Compton.
My phone rings
the next morning,

15:04.282 --> 15:07.423
and my mom is like,
"Frank Black wants to meet you."

15:07.423 --> 15:08.942
Frank Black,
Frank Black?

15:08.942 --> 15:11.117
I grew up listening
to that man's records.

15:11.117 --> 15:12.739
He was the first person
to tell me

15:12.739 --> 15:14.499
I could make money
from my music.

15:14.499 --> 15:15.915
He helped me
with my demo.

15:15.915 --> 15:20.609
He was my manager, mentor,
father figure.

15:20.609 --> 15:23.992
I thought
he was my friend.

15:23.992 --> 15:25.441
[ Sighs ]

15:25.441 --> 15:27.892
It happened slowly.

15:27.892 --> 15:31.240
And you can't really tell
where it begins

15:31.240 --> 15:33.794
or what it really is.

15:33.794 --> 15:35.589
And he makes you
so dependent on him

15:35.589 --> 15:37.522
that questioning
whether it's right or wrong

15:37.522 --> 15:39.110
feels like
you're being ungrateful.

15:39.110 --> 15:42.838
I don't know
if I ever said no.

15:42.838 --> 15:44.840
I let it happen.

15:44.840 --> 15:47.429
And then I thought
it was what I wanted,

15:47.429 --> 15:49.327
so how could I
tell anyone?

15:49.327 --> 15:51.053
You were a child.

15:52.572 --> 15:55.989
I found out I was pregnant
the week my album flopped.

15:55.989 --> 15:57.577
Then he disappeared,

15:57.577 --> 15:59.820
wouldn't return
my calls.

15:59.820 --> 16:02.927
Finally I-I rolled up on him
at a party...

16:02.927 --> 16:06.206
mascara pouring down my face
from the tears.

16:06.206 --> 16:08.346
I told him
I was pregnant.

16:08.346 --> 16:10.900
For a second,
he stopped,

16:10.900 --> 16:13.593
and he looked at me
like I was a person.

16:13.593 --> 16:16.216
I just knew I had gotten through
to him, you know?

16:16.216 --> 16:18.736
Then he just
reached in his pocket,

16:18.736 --> 16:21.911
and he handed me $2,000
and said...

16:21.911 --> 16:25.398
"Go take care
of whoever's it was."

16:25.398 --> 16:26.606
[ Clicks tongue ]

16:26.606 --> 16:28.401
I never
saw him again.

16:28.401 --> 16:30.058
Have you ever thought about
coming forward?

16:30.058 --> 16:31.542
What's the point?

16:31.542 --> 16:33.199
It's done.

16:33.199 --> 16:35.753
♪♪

16:35.753 --> 16:37.410
Naomi says
to start without her.

16:37.410 --> 16:39.722
Something came up
with the Frank Black situation,

16:39.722 --> 16:42.311
so she's meeting
with Zadie.

16:42.311 --> 16:43.381
[ Sighs ]

16:43.381 --> 16:46.798
Why can't people
just let the past go?

16:46.798 --> 16:49.353
I thought Gen Zs
were supposed to be mad woke.

16:49.353 --> 16:51.907
You have been
insanely unsympathetic to Zadie.

16:51.907 --> 16:53.909
Life is full of
these gray areas,

16:53.909 --> 16:56.084
and either
you do something about it

16:56.084 --> 16:58.258
or you put it behind you
and let it go.

16:59.466 --> 17:01.192
Can I crash
at your place tonight?

17:01.192 --> 17:02.814
Thomas and I
got into it,

17:02.814 --> 17:04.575
and I could use
the space.

17:04.575 --> 17:06.128
You know I live at Naomi's
with Muffin and Eric.

17:06.128 --> 17:08.751
Like a hostel?

17:08.751 --> 17:10.408
I'm sure there's a room
in the Ritz.

17:10.408 --> 17:12.410
So you're, what,
two weeks into marriage

17:12.410 --> 17:13.825
and you're already
trying to get out?

17:13.825 --> 17:15.724
Something's not clicking
with Thomas.

17:15.724 --> 17:18.382
He brought me
my favorite carbs

17:18.382 --> 17:21.385
hidden inside
a Louis Vuitton shopping bag.

17:21.385 --> 17:22.765
The bastard.
Ouch.

17:22.765 --> 17:23.939
And then we realized

17:23.939 --> 17:25.216
we never said "I love you"
to each other,

17:25.216 --> 17:26.217
so then he said it.

17:26.217 --> 17:27.425
I didn't like
the way he said it,

17:27.425 --> 17:28.840
so I didn't
say it back --

17:28.840 --> 17:30.601
So this marriage
is basically doomed.

17:30.601 --> 17:32.223
Basically.
I think
she was kidding.

17:32.223 --> 17:33.431
I was.

17:33.431 --> 17:34.743
Oh.

17:34.743 --> 17:37.401
Look, I know you,
and I know what you're doing.

17:37.401 --> 17:40.300
You're trying to sabotage
something that could be good.

17:40.300 --> 17:42.061
Or maybe
everyone was right all along

17:42.061 --> 17:44.270
and I did
something impulsive and dumb

17:44.270 --> 17:46.444
and I should turn back
before I can't.

17:46.444 --> 17:48.067
But you got to try --
hard.

17:48.067 --> 17:49.240
That's all I'm saying.

17:50.345 --> 17:52.588
I got to go soon.
My dad's in town.

17:52.588 --> 17:54.383
I told him I'd join him
for Bible study.

17:54.383 --> 17:55.453
Hold up.

17:55.453 --> 17:57.248
Your mean-ass deacon daddy
is in town?

17:57.248 --> 17:58.525
Chill,
he's my dad.

17:58.525 --> 18:01.356
You said he prays the gayness
out of gay babies.

18:01.356 --> 18:02.840
I'd say
that's pretty mean.

18:02.840 --> 18:04.083
Parents are complicated.

18:04.083 --> 18:05.532
This man raised me.

18:05.532 --> 18:07.500
You're 40,
not 14.

18:07.500 --> 18:09.191
Blood is not
a good enough reason

18:09.191 --> 18:10.537
to have
someone in your life

18:10.537 --> 18:12.091
who doesn't treat you
with respect.

18:12.091 --> 18:13.575
I can't
tell him that.

18:13.575 --> 18:14.921
Both: Yes, you can.

18:16.474 --> 18:18.890
My mom passed
about two years ago,

18:18.890 --> 18:21.652
and it's not like I've been
around very much to help.

18:21.652 --> 18:24.068
So your mom died
and he gets to be an asshole?

18:24.068 --> 18:26.553
When is the world
gonna stop making excuses

18:26.553 --> 18:27.658
for terrible men?

18:27.658 --> 18:29.487
Says the woman
who's running away

18:29.487 --> 18:32.283
from a man
who isn'tan asshole.

18:34.458 --> 18:36.839
Naomi: Leah was 16
in that photo.

18:36.839 --> 18:39.394
That's when Frank
started abusing her.

18:41.741 --> 18:43.639
Why are you
riding me like this?

18:43.639 --> 18:46.366
Because I was onstage with you
when you saw Frank.

18:46.366 --> 18:47.643
I saw
what happened to you.

18:47.643 --> 18:49.818
And I don't think you should
have to give up on music

18:49.818 --> 18:51.509
just because you stood up
for yourself.

18:51.509 --> 18:53.062
We like to think

18:53.062 --> 18:55.927
that the world
is a different place today

18:55.927 --> 18:58.723
than it was in 1999,
but it's not.

18:58.723 --> 19:01.174
Money wins,
power wins.

19:01.174 --> 19:02.762
Men win.

19:02.762 --> 19:06.179
How can you guarantee
that if I tell my story,

19:06.179 --> 19:08.630
other women'll
come forward?

19:09.665 --> 19:11.150
I can't.

19:11.150 --> 19:13.945
But the only thing
I know for sure

19:13.945 --> 19:16.534
is that
if nobodycomes forward,

19:16.534 --> 19:19.434
then Frank gets to do this
to all of his protégés.

19:21.021 --> 19:23.990
Zadie, I found a journalist
that wants to talk to you.

19:23.990 --> 19:25.198
She's good.

19:25.198 --> 19:27.718
She's one of us,
and she will have your back.

19:27.718 --> 19:29.720
♪♪

19:29.720 --> 19:32.067
What do you say?

19:32.067 --> 19:34.069
♪♪

19:34.069 --> 19:36.416
[ Sighs ]

19:36.416 --> 19:39.074
Frank and I were in the studio
late one night.

19:39.074 --> 19:43.699
I got tired, so I told him

19:43.699 --> 19:46.392
I was gonna sleep on the couch
before I got back in the booth.

19:46.392 --> 19:49.222
He said
he'd wake me up in 30.

19:49.222 --> 19:54.227
I remember waking up
because I was cold.

19:54.227 --> 19:57.817
I thought maybe my blanket
had fallen off,

19:57.817 --> 20:00.337
but when I opened my eyes,

20:00.337 --> 20:03.098
I saw that my shirt
had been unbuttoned

20:03.098 --> 20:06.032
and he was trying
to undo my jeans.

20:06.032 --> 20:09.656
I was like,
"Yo, what are you doing?"

20:09.656 --> 20:14.454
And he looked at me so calmly
and asked,

20:14.454 --> 20:16.076
"Why would
you fall asleep here

20:16.076 --> 20:18.941
if you didn't want this
to happen?"

20:18.941 --> 20:22.462
He was so cool
and matter of fact about it

20:22.462 --> 20:23.843
that it threw me off.

20:23.843 --> 20:25.500
I was in shock.

20:25.500 --> 20:29.124
How could it be wrong
if he was so okay about it?

20:29.124 --> 20:32.783
I feel like I blacked out
for a few minutes,

20:32.783 --> 20:38.616
but then the feeling came back
to me when he...did more.

20:38.616 --> 20:42.413
I knew it was wrong,
and I reacted again and again.

20:42.413 --> 20:45.968
It felt like he was just waiting
for me to run out of gas.

20:45.968 --> 20:48.074
He was just so damn calm.

20:48.074 --> 20:51.491
That's the thing
that haunts me the most.

20:51.491 --> 20:53.942
But...

20:53.942 --> 20:56.255
I kept hitting him...

20:56.255 --> 20:57.980
until I had
enough space to run.

20:57.980 --> 21:00.466
It wasn't until the cops
showed up at my place

21:00.466 --> 21:04.366
that I even found out
that I broke his jaw.

21:04.366 --> 21:06.851
They were so damn aggressive

21:06.851 --> 21:10.199
that I thought I'd done
something wrong.

21:10.199 --> 21:14.549
I got raped and arrested
on the same night.

21:14.549 --> 21:17.310
After a few hours in jail,

21:17.310 --> 21:21.452
my lawyer came and he said he
could get the charges dropped

21:21.452 --> 21:24.386
as long as the story stayed
with me, so that's what I did.

21:24.386 --> 21:27.907
But after I got out, no producer
would give me a track

21:27.907 --> 21:31.635
'cause I was the hood chick
that breaks producers' jaws.

21:31.635 --> 21:34.569
You know
who hired my attorney?

21:34.569 --> 21:37.226
Frank.
That's the game.

21:37.226 --> 21:39.263
That's what Frank Black
did to me.

21:39.263 --> 21:41.196
I am so sorry
that this happened to you.

21:41.196 --> 21:43.405
I don't even
have the words.

21:43.405 --> 21:46.477
I don't need sympathy.
I don't need an apology.

21:46.477 --> 21:50.826
I need Frank Black
to be held accountable.

21:50.826 --> 21:52.932
I promise to do my part.

21:52.932 --> 21:57.143
♪♪

21:57.143 --> 21:59.283
[ Footsteps approaching ]

21:59.283 --> 22:02.459
What a glorious morning
to topple the patriarchy.

22:02.459 --> 22:03.667
Right.

22:03.667 --> 22:06.842
Zadie's story on Frank
is supposed to run today.

22:06.842 --> 22:08.982
It's already out.

22:08.982 --> 22:14.505
♪♪

22:14.505 --> 22:20.028
♪♪

22:23.203 --> 22:27.553
I told you
I didn't want to do this.

22:27.553 --> 22:31.971
I knew
this is how it would go.

22:31.971 --> 22:34.180
"It would be impossible
not to be moved

22:34.180 --> 22:37.977
by Lady Z's account of
the events nearly 20 years ago,

22:37.977 --> 22:41.498
but we'd also be foolish
not to question the timing

22:41.498 --> 22:44.811
and what she stands to gain from
spinning a different narrative

22:44.811 --> 22:47.089
than the one
we've previously known."

22:47.089 --> 22:49.575
Frank's people
must've gotten to them.

22:49.575 --> 22:50.955
I never should've listened
to you.

22:50.955 --> 22:51.991
You did the right thing,

22:51.991 --> 22:53.579
no matter what
this article says.

22:53.579 --> 22:57.410
It's so easy to lead the charge
when it costs younothing.

22:58.963 --> 23:00.655
I'm sorry.

23:00.655 --> 23:02.208
You dragged me
back into this!

23:02.208 --> 23:05.107
And now all your lame,
self-serving ass

23:05.107 --> 23:07.800
is offering
is a weak apology?

23:07.800 --> 23:11.044
You are obsessed
with fixing problems

23:11.044 --> 23:12.908
that ain't got nothing
to do with you.

23:12.908 --> 23:14.600
This is never
gonna change.

23:14.600 --> 23:16.256
This is the world
we live in.

23:16.256 --> 23:20.364
The only thing that people
like me, the victims, can do

23:20.364 --> 23:24.575
is bury it inside and move on,
because the result is the same.

23:24.575 --> 23:27.820
Now I have to live
with the pain again.

23:27.820 --> 23:30.995
I will not shed another tear
over this.

23:30.995 --> 23:35.206
Frank Black doesn't get
anything else from me.

23:35.206 --> 23:38.209
Done with you
and Nasty Girl Records.

23:39.279 --> 23:40.902
No, wait.

23:40.902 --> 23:42.110
[ Door opens, closes ]

23:42.110 --> 23:45.216
"In an effort to salvage
the shambles of her career,

23:45.216 --> 23:48.081
Zadie capitalizes
on the Me Too movement

23:48.081 --> 23:50.152
by reinventing herself
as a victim,

23:50.152 --> 23:53.362
coincidentally, just in time
to debut new music."

23:53.362 --> 23:56.227
I mean, not only have
I ruined a woman's life,

23:56.227 --> 23:59.748
I might've just tanked
Nasty Girl Records.

23:59.748 --> 24:02.164
♪♪

24:02.164 --> 24:03.511
Naomi.

24:03.511 --> 24:09.827
♪♪

24:09.827 --> 24:11.450
[ Exhales deeply ]

24:11.450 --> 24:12.899
[ Clears throat ]

24:12.899 --> 24:15.212
Okay.

24:15.212 --> 24:17.145
Hey, Daddy.

24:17.145 --> 24:18.664
It's me.

24:18.664 --> 24:20.079
[ Thudding ]

24:20.079 --> 24:22.530
[ Gasps ] Daddy?

24:22.530 --> 24:26.361
♪♪

24:26.361 --> 24:27.742
What?

24:27.742 --> 24:29.502
[ Gasps ]
Daddy!

24:29.502 --> 24:31.953
Daddy. Come on.

24:31.953 --> 24:33.541
[ Grunts ]

24:33.541 --> 24:35.750
[ Slurring ] Jill, baby,
you're home.

24:35.750 --> 24:36.751
[ Grunts ]

24:36.751 --> 24:39.788
I'm so glad you're home.

24:39.788 --> 24:43.067
Come on,
let's get you in bed.

24:43.067 --> 24:44.206
Come on, come on.

24:44.206 --> 24:47.382
Hey.

24:47.382 --> 24:49.108
Are you gonna cancel
the showcase

24:49.108 --> 24:50.212
now that Zadie's out?

24:50.212 --> 24:51.490
I'm not sure it matters.

24:51.490 --> 24:53.215
I mean, we can't put on
the showcase

24:53.215 --> 24:55.390
when our number-one draft pick
just quit,

24:55.390 --> 24:57.219
and Muffin,
with her new flow,

24:57.219 --> 24:58.911
is gonna have to build
a fan base again.

24:58.911 --> 25:00.291
You should go home
and do something fun

25:00.291 --> 25:02.777
with your, uh...husband?

25:02.777 --> 25:05.987
I'm sorry, I --
I'm still getting used to it.

25:05.987 --> 25:08.127
I'm still getting used to you
being a dad.

25:08.127 --> 25:09.300
We grown now.

25:09.300 --> 25:11.682
Are we?
Do we really change?

25:11.682 --> 25:16.480
We say we do,
but is that really real?

25:16.480 --> 25:18.378
It's too early
for the deep stuff.

25:18.378 --> 25:22.866
Thomas told me he loved me,

25:22.866 --> 25:27.905
and, uh, instead of saying
it back, I ran away.

25:27.905 --> 25:29.597
I found issues.

25:29.597 --> 25:32.185
You know, usually brides get
cold feet before the wedding.

25:32.185 --> 25:34.774
I've only said it
to two people.

25:38.675 --> 25:40.987
Do you?
Love him?

25:40.987 --> 25:43.058
I don't know him.

25:43.058 --> 25:45.889
That summer "Nasty Girl"
dropped was wild.

25:45.889 --> 25:49.858
I went from being homeless,
living in my car

25:49.858 --> 25:53.448
to flying private
to St. Barts with you.

25:53.448 --> 25:54.587
We had fun.

25:54.587 --> 25:56.589
The other person I said
"I love you" to

25:56.589 --> 25:59.074
was a woman
impersonating my mom.

25:59.074 --> 26:00.835
The only love I know
is wrong.

26:00.835 --> 26:04.977
It's crazy, it's angry.

26:04.977 --> 26:07.358
It's confusing.

